This paper discusses the privacy threat of browser fingerprinting, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and cybercrime (cs.CY). The paper also mentions the development of a browser extension, which could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the crawling of websites, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI) category.
